OL,4,CClimate change: Carbon 'surge' expected
OL,5,Cin post-Covid energy boom
OL,6, The International Energy Agency (IEA)
OL,7, is predicting a major surge in CO2
OL,8, emissions from energy this year, as the
OL,9, world rebounds from the pandemic.
OL,11,FTotal energy emissions for 2021 will
OL,12,Fstill be slightly lower than in 2019,
OL,13,Fthe agency says.
OL,15,FBut CO2 will rise by the second largest
OL,16,Fannual amount on record.
OL,18,FThe use of coal in Asia is expected to
OL,19,Fbe key: the IEA says it will push
OL,20,Fglobal demand up by 4.5%, taking it
OL,21,Fclose to the global peak seen in 2014.
